LA Weekly named Stelling no. 2 on a list of "12 L.A. Comedy Acts to Watch in 2013." Patton Oswalt listed Beth as one of his favorite up-and-coming comics during his AMA on Reddit. Buzzfeed.com says she's one of "14 Comedians Who You Should Be Paying Attention To." 

Beth was a New Face of Comedy at the Just for Laughs Comedy Festival in Montreal and returned to the festival last summer to record HBO Canada's "Funny As Hell" with Jon Dore.

Beth was deemed one of the "Top 18 Women You Should Be Following On Twitter" by Huffington Post. Nerdist.com has been a big supporter of Beth, including her in their "Four Funny Female Comedians You Need to Know" alongside Shelby Fero, Tig Notaro and Ali Wong. Byron won the Big Sky International Comedy Competition and was named by LA Weekly as a "Comedy Act to Watch in 2013". He was also featured as a New Face at the prestigious Just for Laughs Comedy Festival in 2013. Byron performed on the side stage at the Oddball Comedy Festival in 2013, only to be promoted to the main stage in 2014, sharing the spotlight with Louis CK, Jim Gaffigan, Sarah Silverman and others. Byron's appeared on The Eric Andre Show on Adult Swim, Comedy Central's Adam Devine's House Party, on the reboot of BET's Comic View and he made his late night debut on The Pete Holmes Show.
